IHE_PCC_MAPS

The official URL for this implementation guide is: 

https://profiles.ihe.net/PCC/mAPS/ImplementationGuide/ihe.pcc.maps

Antepartum Summary is a content profile that defines the structure for the aggregation of significant events, diagnoses, and plans of care derived from the visits over the course of an antepartum episode.

resource.name: Antapartum Summary
resource.description:
Antepartum Summary is a content profile that defines the structure for the aggregation of significant events, diagnoses, and plans of care derived from the visits over the course of an antepartum episode. 
It is represented in part by Estimated Due Dates and a Visit Summary Flowsheet, in which the aggregated data from the ambulatory office visits is recorded, as well as allergies, advance directives, care plans, 
and selected histories are provided. The Antepartum Summary represents a summary of the most critical information to an antepartum care provider regarding the status of a patient’s pregnancy.

resource.name: Number of Abortions
resource.description:
Number of pregnancies terminated before 20 weeks of gestation calculated from the date of onset of last menses [or equivalent date estimated from ultrasound or other measurement or from 
data derived from assisted fertilization procedure].

resource.name: Number of Abortions Induced
resource.description: Number of intentional medical or surgical terminations of pregnancies before 20 weeks of gestation. [Includes elective and therapeutic terminations.

resource.name: Number of Abortions Spontanious
resource.description: Number of unintentional terminations of pregnancies before 20 weeks of gestation. [Excludes induced terminations].

resource.name: Number of Ectopic Pregnancy
resource.description: Number of Ectopic Pregnancies

resource.name: Number of Live Births
resource.description:
Total number of live births. [Complete expulsion or extraction from the mother if a product of human conception, irrespective of duration of pregnancy, which, after expulsion or extraction, breathes or shows 
any other evidence of life such as heart beat.

resource.name: Number Of Other Pregnancy Outcomes
resource.description:
Other pregnancy outcomes # Includes perinatal death, small for gestational age/intrauterine growth restricted birth. History of pregnancies continuing into the 20th week of gestation and resulting in 
any of the listed outcomes. Perinatal death includes fetal and neonatal deaths.

resource.name: Number of Pregnancies
resource.description: Total number of times the patient has been pregnant including the present pregnancy.

resource.name: Number Of Prenatal Visits For This Pregnancy
resource.description: Do not include visits for laboratory and other testing in which a physician or health care professional did not examine or counsel the pregnant woman Access the most recent prenatal records available. If up-to-date records are not available, contact the prenatal care provider for the most current information. Count the prenatal visits recorded in the record. Exclude visits for laboratory and other tests or classes in which the mother was not seen by a physician or other health care professional for pregnancy-related care. If it is not clear whether the mother was seen by a physician or other health care professional, include the visit(s) in the total number.

resource.name: Number of Preterm Births
resource.description: Total number of children whose birth occurred through the end of the last day of the 37th week (259th day) following onset of the last menstrual period.

resource.name: Number Of Previous Cesarean Deliveries
resource.description: Previous delivery by extracting the fetus, placenta, and membranes through an incision in the mother’s abdominal and uterine walls.

resource.name: Number Of Previous Live Births Now Dead
resource.description: Previous delivery by extracting the fetus, placenta, and membranes through an incision in the mother’s abdominal and uterine walls.

resource.name: Number of Stillborn Births
resource.description: Number of Stillborn Births

resource.name: Number of Total Births
resource.description:
Total number of births including abortions, stillbirths and live births. [Note: Because of multiple gestation this number may be greater than the number of abortions plus parity, 
the number of times the uterus is emptied of a viable pregnancy.
